    <question number="1">
        <prompt>What were sea voyages like during colonial exploration?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Quick and comfortable</option>
            <option letter="b">Long and dangerous</option>
            <option letter="c">Only for military ships</option>
            <option letter="d">Limited to coastal waters</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Colonial sea voyages were typically long, dangerous journeys that could take months and faced threats from weather, disease, and pirates.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question number="2">
        <prompt>What was the average length of a transatlantic voyage in the colonial period?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">One week</option>
            <option letter="b">Two to three months</option>
            <option letter="c">Six months</option>
            <option letter="d">One year</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>A typical transatlantic voyage in the colonial period took about two to three months, depending on weather and conditions.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question number="3">
        <prompt>What was the primary challenge of colonial sea voyages?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Entertainment</option>
            <option letter="b">Navigation</option>
            <option letter="c">Cooking</option>
            <option letter="d">Communication</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Navigation was the primary challenge, as ships relied on basic tools like compasses, astrolabes, and celestial navigation.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question number="4">
        <prompt>What type of ship was most commonly used for colonial voyages?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Steamships</option>
            <option letter="b">Sailing ships</option>
            <option letter="c">Rowboats</option>
            <option letter="d">Submarines</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Sailing ships, particularly galleons and merchant vessels, were the primary means of colonial transportation across oceans.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question number="5">
        <prompt>What was a major cause of death during colonial sea voyages?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Shark attacks</option>
            <option letter="b">Disease and malnutrition</option>
            <option letter="c">Boredom</option>
            <option letter="d">Homesickness</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Disease (especially scurvy) and malnutrition were major causes of death during long sea voyages in the colonial period.</explanation>
    </question>
